Key Match Events: Mohamed Bayo scored a last-gasp winner with just 22 seconds remaining in stoppage time.
Equatorial Guinea was reduced to 10 men after Federico Bikoro received a red card for a high-footed challenge.
Emilio Nsue missed a penalty kick after a foul by Sekou Sylla on Iban Salvador.
Post-Match Reflections: Guinea's win sends them into the last eight of the Africa Cup of Nations.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was noted for a lengthy VAR check and poor overall quality.
